{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WJC2djKFm3Jq6mvrN25tCF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `app-data` index shards are marked as `CLUSTER_RECOVERED` with `no_valid_shard_copy`. This means ES believes there's no valid copy of the shard data in any node in the cluster.\n\nThis could be because:\n1. The `app-data` index's shards were previously stored on the `es-data-new` nodes (not on the main `elasticsearch` nodes)\n2. The PVCs for `es-data-new` might have had that data\n\nWait, but earlier when I queried `app-data`, it showed 3 documents and returned them fine. The cluster was green with 5 nodes and all 4 shards were assigned. \nWhen I scaled down `es-data-new`, those nodes left the cluster. If the primary shard of `app-data` was on one of those nodes, the data is still in the PVCs but the cluster can't access it anymore. The replica should have been on one of the main nodes, unless both copies ended up on the `es-data-new` nodes—which would explain why the cluster can't find any valid shard copy now.\n\nI should check the PVCs for `es-data-new` to see if the data is actually there, and consider temporarily bringing those pods back to allow the cluster to relocate the shards. But wait—I already queried `app-data` from elasticsearch-0 and got 3 documents back, so the data might actually be on the main nodes' disks. The issue is that ES doesn't recognize it after the restart, as shown by the `\"store\": {\"found\": false}` response. This suggests the data was only on the `es-data-new` nodes.\n\nLooking at the StatefulSet configuration, each elasticsearch pod has its own PVC, and `es-data-new` has separate PVCs too. When I queried earlier, the request was routed to the appropriate node, but now that those nodes are gone, the shards are unavailable. I'm thinking about scaling `es-data-new` back up temporarily—though there's a version mismatch since it's on 8.11.0 while the main cluster is on 8.11.1.\n\nIn Elasticsearch, minor version differences within the same major version should be compatible during rolling upgrades, so 8.11.0 and 8.11.1 nodes should be able to form a cluster together. But I need to verify whether the `app-data` shard data is still intact in the PVCs of the elasticsearch nodes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":901,"cache_read_input_tokens":40809,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":901},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1eb9122f-e4ea-4e6c-a91d-033b112413ed","uuid":"b832c67d-a484-4270-abc1-a96303f03b11","request_id":"req_011Ccf6jcjSGgHHvLUYaNPAt"}
